The paper proposes a method for visualizing large multi-dimensional data sets using parallel coordinates plot and focuses on addressing the challenges of visual clutter and overplotting. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Database (cs.DB) sub-categories. The proposed method also uses density-based confluent drawing to visualize clusters and edges, which falls under the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of interactions to control the data binning process, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of a web-based visual analytics application, which falls under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
